# Auth Rules (NextAuth.js v5)

## Setup
- Use NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) with Prisma adapter
- Credentials provider (email + password) as primary
- bcrypt for password hashing
- JWT strategy for sessions

## Roles
- `ADMIN` — full access, manage everything
- `CURATOR` — review homework, manage assigned courses
- `USER` — student, access enrolled courses only

## Authorization Pattern
```typescript
// In Server Actions / Server Components
const session = await auth();
if (!session) redirect("/login");
if (session.user.role !== "ADMIN") throw new Error("Forbidden");
```

## Middleware
- Protect `/admin/*` routes — ADMIN + CURATOR only
- Protect `/learn/*` routes — authenticated users only
- Public routes: `/`, `/login`, `/register`, `/catalog`

## Session Extension
- Extend session with `role` and `id` fields
- Type-safe session via module augmentation in `types/next-auth.d.ts`
